This paper discusses the end-to-end latency of HetNets with mm-wave communications, which is a topic related to network optimization and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the optimization of delay problems, which is related to information theory, and the use of cooperative networking, which is related to control systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of mm-wave radios, which is related to hardware and communication technologies, and therefore cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category.
